&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="path-reconstruction"&gt;path reconstruction&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;every time a shorter dist for a node is found (relaxation), record the source node to this node of current edge.&lt;/p&gt;</description><dc:creator>K4i</dc:creator><media:content url="https://k4i.top//images/icons/bellman-ford-example.png" medium="image"><media:title type="html">featured image</media:title></media:content><category>shortest-path</category><category>Data-Structure-and-Algorithm</category></item><item><title>Cycle Finding Algorithms</title><link>https://k4i.top/posts/cycle-finding-algorithms/</link><pubDate>Tue, 19 Dec 2023 00:27:00 +0800</pubDate><author>sky_io@outlook.com (K4i)</author><atom:modified>Tue, 19 Dec 2023 00:32:30 +0800</atom:modified><guid>https://k4i.top/posts/cycle-finding-algorithms/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="floyd-s-tortoise-and-hare"&gt;Floyd&amp;rsquo;s tortoise and hare&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src="https://k4i.top/images/posts/cycle-finding/tortoise-and-hare.svg"
alt="Figure 1: tortoise and hare"&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="figure-number"&gt;Figure 1: &lt;/span&gt;tortoise and hare&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;hare and tortoise both starts from point &lt;strong&gt;Start&lt;/strong&gt;, at speed of \(2\) and \(1\) respectively. They&amp;rsquo;ll meet at some point in the cycle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;when they meet, hare traveled \(S_2 - S_{1}\) more points than tortoise. We have: (\(\lambda\) is the cycle length)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\[&lt;br /&gt;
S_{2} - S_{1} = 0 = S_{1} = x + m \pmod{\lambda}&lt;br /&gt;
\]&lt;/p&gt;</description><dc:creator>K4i</dc:creator><media:content url="https://k4i.top//images/icons/TortoiseHare.jpg" medium="image"><media:title type="html">featured image</media:title></media:content><category>cycle-finding</category><category>Data-Structure-and-Algorithm</category></item></channel></rss>